      "content": "The effectiveness of nonviolent resistance is a historical and philosophical debate, but it was undeniably the most strategically powerful approach used. Nonviolence allowed the movement to gain massive moral high ground, compelling national attention and sympathy from the public and federal government. Critics who argue it caused division often overlook how the violent resistance of opposing groups was the primary force driving the need for federal intervention. Ultimately, the disciplined, strategic use of nonviolence proved to be the most effective catalyst for legislative change.",
